I'm experiencing the same issue on my new Mac book pro 15". It's annoying. The first load time on my Mac is 10x times slower than my 4 years old Linux laptop with the same configuration. Both machine are having SSD.

@lazywei Would you please let me know how to generate the time report as you did? I want to measure the time differences.

The other thing is my Mac has FileVault enabled and Antivirus software (Sophos) installed -- due to company policy -- don't know how much impact caused by these two.

@liujoey Thanks for the followup, that makes sense. In my experience, corporate AV on Windows caused a 3x slowdown for many `git` operations. Is `git` faster for you after disabling the AV? 

AV "realtime inspection" inserts itself on every process start, so programs like `git` which often spawn  child-processes will be slower, and that would also be the case for `nvim` spawning `python` processes. Are you able to request exceptions for e.g. python?

Note also that setting `g:python_host_prog` and/or `g:python3_host_prog` should help (see `:help g:python_host_prog`).
